### Next Steps (Case Study 3)

**v_shared_allocation** — the most complex view in Phase 3
- Business scenario: Split shared platform costs across BUs using allocation_weights table
- New SQL concepts: JOIN (one-to-many), calculated columns (total_cost × weight_value), CTEs
- Design challenge: One shared cost → multiple output rows (one per BU receiving allocation)
- Pool types: P001 (usage-based), P002 (flat), P003 (headcount-weighted)

**Learning objectives for next session:**
- Understanding one-to-many JOINs (1 cost record joins to 4 BU weight records = 4 output rows)
- Calculated columns in SELECT (multiplication across joined tables)
- Deciding which business_unit to display (from allocation_weights, not from original cost)
